The app is successfully installed and launched on the iOS device.

Test Case Title: App Launch and Onboarding

Test Case ID: ONB-001

Description: Verify that the app launches successfully and provides a smooth onboarding experience for new users.

Preconditions:

The app is installed on the device.

Test Steps:

1. Open the app by tapping on its icon.
2. Observe the app's launch time and check for any delays or crashes.
3. On the first app launch (for new users), the app should initiate the onboarding process. For returning users, skip to step 6.
4. During onboarding, verify the following:
   - User registration or login options are available.
   - App permissions requests (e.g., location, notifications) are presented with clear explanations.
   - User data collection and privacy policy agreement (if applicable).
5. Complete the onboarding process, including user registration or login, accepting permissions, and agreeing to the privacy policy (if applicable).
6. After onboarding (for returning users), the app should display its main interface or home screen.

Expected Results:

- The app should launch without any noticeable delays or crashes.
- Onboarding for new users should be smooth and intuitive, with clear explanations for permissions and data collection.
- Returning users should be directly taken to the app's main interface.

Actual Result:
- Application launches without any noticeable delay or crashes.
- Smooth onboarding for new users, clear explanation for permissions and data collection.
- Returning users are directly taken to the app's main interface.

Test Case 1: User Registration/Login

Test Case Title: User Registration and Login

Test Case ID: FT-01

Description: Verify that users can successfully register for an account and log in to the application.

Preconditions:
- The application is installed and launched.
- The user is on the registration/login screen on the profile page.

Test Steps:

1. Log in options: Apple account, Facebook account, Google account, email address.
2. Click on "Continue with email."
3. Enter a valid user email address that is available to receive a confirmation code.
4. Click "Send email."
5. Enter the confirmation code that was sent.
6. Verify that the user is successfully logged in.
7. Verify that the user's name or profile picture (if applicable) is displayed on the home screen.

Expected Results:

- The user should be able to complete the registration and login processes without any errors.
- After successful login, the user should land on the profile screen with their name or profile picture visible.

Actual Result:
- The user is able to complete the registration and login process without any errors.
- After login, the user lands on the profile screen page with their name and profile picture visible.

Test Case 2: News Article Retrieval

Test Case Title: News Article Retrieval

Test Case ID: FT-02

Description: Verify that users can retrieve and view news articles from various sources.

Preconditions:
- The user is logged in and on the application's home screen.

Test Steps:

1. Navigate to the "News" or "Articles" section of the application.
2. Select a news category (e.g., "Technology," "Sports," "Politics").
3. Click on a news article.
4. Verify that the article opens and displays the content.
5. Check for the presence of images, text formatting, and any embedded media (if applicable).
6. Scroll through the article to ensure smooth navigation.
7. Use any provided interaction features.

Expected Results:

- Users should be able to select and view news articles from different categories.
- Articles should be displayed correctly, including any multimedia elements.
- Navigation within articles and interaction features should work as expected.

Actual Result:
- User is able to select and view news articles from different categories.
- Articles are displayed correctly, including multimedia elements.

Test Case 3: Search Functionality

Test Case Title: Search Functionality

Test Case ID: FT-03

Description: Verify that users can search for specific news articles or topics.

Preconditions:
- The user is logged in and on the application's home screen.

Test Steps:

1. Locate the search bar within the application.
2. Enter a search query (e.g., a keyword or topic).
3. Click the "Search" or "Submit" button.
4. Review the search results.
5. Click on a search result to view the corresponding article.
6. Verify that the article opens and displays the content.

Expected Results:

- Users should be able to search for articles based on their queries.
- The search results should be relevant to the query.
- Clicking on a search result should open the corresponding article.

Actual Result:
- Users are able to search for articles based on their queries.
- The search result is relevant to the query.
- Clicking on the search result opens the corresponding articles.

Localization Testing

Test Case 1: Language Selection

Test Case Title: Language Selection

Test Case ID: LOC-01

Description: Verify that the application allows users to select their preferred language and that the app's content and user interface are displayed in the selected language.

Preconditions:
- The application is installed and launched.
- The user is on the settings screen (if applicable).

Test Steps:

1. Navigate to the application's settings.
2. Locate the edition selection option.
3. Select a different language from the available options (e.g., United States or Japanese).
4. Confirm the language change by saving the selection.
5. Verify that the app's content, including news articles and user interface elements, is displayed in the selected language.

Expected Results:

- After selecting a language, all app content should be displayed in the chosen language.

Actual Result:
- Selecting a language changes all app content to the chosen language.

Test Case Title: Date and Time Format

Test Case ID: LOC-02

Description: Verify that date and time formats are correctly localized based on the selected region and language.

Preconditions:
- The application is installed and launched.
- The user has selected a language edition.

Test Steps:

1. Navigate to the application's settings or preferences.
2. Verify that there's an option to set the language edition.
3. Change the region or country setting to a different location (from the United States to Japan).
4. Access news articles and check for the correct date and time formats (e.g., MM/DD/YYYY to DD/MM/YYYY).
5. Verify that the date and time in the user interface (e.g., timestamps) are also updated accordingly.

Expected Results:

- Changing the region should update date and time formats in both news articles and the user interface.

Actual Result:
- Changing the region updates the dates and time format in both the news article and the user interface.

Test Case Title: Currency Display

Test Case ID: LOC-03

Description: Verify that the application displays currency symbols and formats correctly for the selected region and language.

Preconditions:
- The application is installed and launched.
- The user has selected a language edition.

Test Steps:

1. Navigate to the application's settings screen.
2. Verify that there's an option to set the region or country.
3. Change the region or country setting to a different location (e.g., from the United States to Japan).
4. Access financial news articles or sections that involve currency information.
5. Verify that currency symbols and formatting are displayed correctly.

Expected Results:

- Changing the edition should update currency symbols and formatting in financial news articles.

Actual Result:
- Changing the language edition updates the currency symbols and formatting in financial news articles.

Test Case Title: Content Localization

Test Case ID: LOC-04

Description: Verify that news articles, headlines, and other content are correctly translated and culturally adapted for the selected language edition.

Preconditions:
- The application is installed and launched.
- The user has selected a language edition.

Test Steps:

1. Access news articles in different categories.
2. Verify that headlines, article content, and any related text (e.g., captions, summaries) are translated accurately into the selected language.
3. Check for cultural adaptation, such as using appropriate terms, references, and context for the region.

Expected Results:

- All news content should be correctly translated and culturally adapted to the selected language and region.

Actual Result:
- All news content is correctly translated and culturally adapted to the selected language and region.

Test Case Title: App Feature (Local) Testing

Test Case ID: LOC-05

Description: Verify that you can find local stories in your area.

Preconditions:
- The application is installed and launched.
- The user has selected the local screen.

Test Steps:

1. Click on the local screen.
2. Enter your city or ZIP code or click "Use device location."
3. Verify that you can see local stories in your area.

Expected Result:
- All news content and stories should be specific to your area.

Actual Result (Japan or US ZIP code) iOS:
- US and Japan ZIP codes work perfectly.

Actual Result (other countries) iOS:
- ZIP code is restricted in some countries.
- When "Use device location" is clicked, it does not return any error message informing the user of the unavailability of that feature; it only bounces back.

Refer to the issues for images and videos.

Actual Result (Japan or US ZIP code) Android:
- US and Japan ZIP codes work perfectly.

Actual Result (other countries) Android:
- ZIP code is restricted in some countries.
- Not all city or ZIP codes are accepted.
- When "Use device location" is clicked, it returns a location updated.

Refer to the issues for images and videos.
